%N A396346 a(0) = 0; for n > 0, a(n) = a(n-1) - n if nonnegative and not already in the sequence, otherwise a(n) = a(n-1) + n - 1.
%C A396346 Every natural number appears in the sequence for n >= 2. Specifically, any natural number that is not a term of A396345 appears exactly once, while the terms of A396345 appear at least once.
%H A396346 Seiichi Manyama, <a href="/A396346/b396346.txt">Table of n, a(n) for n = 0..8969</a>
%F A396346 For n >= 3, a(n) = A396345(m) if n - m == 0 mod 2, and a(n) = A396345(m) - n otherwise, where m is the unique index satisfying A396344(m) <= n < A396344(m+1).
%e A396346   m | a(n) for A396344(m) <= n < A396344(m+1)
